@lguohan 
I moved all the options in the current inclusion file to [amd64], do you think that's ok? CENTEC arm64 ARCH depends none of them.
Or do you need to keep the x86 and ARM kernel options as consistent as possible?

@jostar-yang, thank you for adding the support. According to the criteria in https://github.com/Azure/sonic-linux-kernel/blob/master/README.md, patches have to be sent upstream.

> Existing kernel modules need to be patched and those patches are available in upstream.

Have you done that already? Please also add the tag `Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org`, so it will be also added to the stable and LTS series.
